Package: mrtransport
Title: Transportability Testing for Mendelian Randomization
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Elliot", "Tower", email = "elliot@elliottower.ai",
                   role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Tests whether stratified Mendelian randomization (MR) causal
    effect estimates are transportable across populations. For scalar effects,
    implements Cochran's Q with post-hoc power analysis, leave-one-out
    sensitivity, and alpha-sweep diagnostics. For vector-valued effects
    (multiple traits at one locus), implements the multivariate sheaf Q
    statistic that detects effect vector rotation invisible to per-trait
    scalar Q tests. Includes locus classification (concordant, rotation-only,
    component-only), rotation angle computation, and simulation utilities
    for benchmarking.
